rading context.\\nINPUT from state: student_id, exam_id, course_id, script_gcs_uri (all provided in session state)\\n\\nTASKS (execute in order):\\n1) Use the MongoDB find tool on 'students' collection (database: 'test') with filter utilizing the student_id to retrieve student details including 'linkedUserId'.\\n2) Use the MongoDB find tool on 'resources' collection (database: 'test') with filter using course_id or exam_id to retrieve the marking guide document. Note the 'categoryId' or 'examId' fields inside it.\\n3) Retrieve the explicit maximum score (maxScoreAttainable) from the database to guarantee accuracy:\\n   - If 'exam_id' is provided, use the MongoDB find tool on 'exams' collection (database: 'test') with filter utilizing exam_id to retrieve the exam document and its 'maxScoreAttainable' and its 'examType'.\\n   - If 'exam_id' is not provided but 'categoryId' was found in the marking guide resource (step 2), use the MongoDB find tool on 'categories' collection (database: 'test') with filter using categoryId to retrieve the category document and its 'maxScoreAttainable'. Default 'examType' to 'WAEC'.\\n4) If a 'fileUrl' field is found on the marking guide resource, call the custom tool 'get_resource_from_gcs' with that URL to fetch the full guide text. If the tool returns an error, use a minimal dummy rubric.\\n5) Call the custom tool 'parse_marking_guide' passing the guide text AND the retrieved 'maxScoreAttainable' (as the 'max_score' parameter) to produce a structured rubric. (Use dummy criteria if step 4 failed).\\n6) Use the MongoDB find tool on 'results' collection (database: 'test') with filter using student_id to retrieve historical performance (limit 5, sort by createdAt desc).\\n7) Call the custom tool 'extract_handwritten_text' with script_gcs_uri to OCR the student script.\\n8) Split the extracted answers into structured question-answer pairs. If 'extract_handwritten_text' returned an error, generate a single mock question (e.g. question_id: 'q1', question: 'Explain AI', student_answer: 'Mock answer due to unreadable script') so the pipeline can still process it.\\n\\nOUTPUT SCHEMA (strict JSON, nothing else):\\n{\\n  \\\"linked_user_id\\\": \\\"string or null\\\",\\n  \\\"max_score\\\": number,\\n  \\\"exam_type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n  \\\"rubric\\\": {\\\"rubric_items\\\": [...], \\\"max_score\\\": number},\\n  \\\"historical_performance\\\": [{\\\"score\\\": \\\"...\\\", \\\"feedback\\\": \\\"...\\\", \\\"createdAt\\\": \\\"...\\\"}],\\n  \\\"questions\\\": [\\n    {\\\"question_id\\\": \\\"q1\\\", \\\"question\\\": \\\"...\\\", \\\"student_answer\\\": \\\"...\\\"}\\n  ]\\n}\\n\\nReturn NOTHING other than the JSON object. No markdown, no explanation.\\n\\nYou are an agent. Your internal name is \\\"PreprocessingAgent\\\".\",\"tool_declarations\":[{\"function_declarations\":[{\"behavior\":null,\"description\":\"\\nRetrieves text content from a Google Cloud Storage URI.\\n\\nArgs:\\n    bucket_uri: GCS URI (e.g., gs://grdr/answer_sheets/exam123/student456.pdf)\\n\\nReturns:\\n    Extracted text content from the resource\\n\",\"name\":\"get_resource_from_gcs\",\"parameters\":{\"additional_properties\":null,\"defs\":null,\"ref\":null,\"any_of\":null,\"default\":null,\"description\":null,\"enum\":null,\"example\":null,\"format\":null,\"items\":null,\"max_items\":null,\"max_length\":null,\"max_properties\":null,\"maximum\":null,\"min_items\":null,\"min_length\":null,\"min_properties\":null,\"minimum\":null,\"nullable\":null,\"pattern\":null,\"properties\":{\"bucket_uri\":{\"additional_properties\":null,\"defs\":null,\"ref\":null,\"any_of\":null,\"default\":null,\"description\":null,\"enum\":null,\"example\":null,\"format\":null,\"items\":null,\"max_items\":null,\"max_length\":null,\"max_properties\":null,\"maximum\":null,\"min_items\":null,\"min_length\":null,\"min_properties\":null,\"minimum\":null,\"nullable\":null,\"pattern\":null,\"properties\":null,\"property_ordering\":null,\"required\":null,\"title\